# Patterns (ECC-inspired, FlexiQueue-aligned)

## Thin controllers, explicit services

- Controllers: **HTTP concerns** — auth, validation (Form Requests), response shape, status codes.
- **Business rules** live in **`app/Services/`** (and related domain code), easy to test without full HTTP stack.

Per **`stack-conventions.mdc`**: no heavy logic in controllers.

## DTOs and explicit shapes

- Replace **large associative arrays** crossing boundaries with **DTOs** or typed structures when it clarifies contracts (requests, commands, external API payloads).
- Value objects fit **money**, **identifiers**, and **invariants** (format, range).

## Dependency injection

- Prefer **constructor injection** and narrow interfaces; avoid hidden **service locator** usage in new code.

## API response shape

- Keep **consistent JSON** conventions across endpoints (success / error fields, validation errors, pagination metadata when applicable).
- Follow **`docs/architecture/08-API-SPEC-PHASE1.md`** and project error-handling docs when they apply.

## Repository pattern

- Use a **repository** when multiple storage backends or complex query encapsulation justify it.
- Laravel **Eloquent + query scopes** is often enough; don’t add repositories by default if they only wrap one model.

## Reference implementations

When adding **unfamiliar** stack pieces, prefer **official or well-maintained** examples, then adapt—don’t copy opaque “starter” code blindly.
